{"questionId":"33230283","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The time, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> minutes, taken to complete a jigsaw puzzle can be modelled by a normal&nbsp;distribution with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi></math> and standard deviation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>It is found that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;of times taken to complete the jigsaw puzzle are longer than&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>36</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;minutes.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Use&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>32</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>29</mn></math> in the remainder of the question.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Six randomly chosen people complete the jigsaw puzzle.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that at least five of them will take more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math> minutes to&nbsp;complete the jigsaw puzzle.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> represent the number of people out of the six who take more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math> minutes to complete the jigsaw puzzle</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi><mo>~</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6049</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p>for example,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>(A1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>241</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[3</strong><strong>&nbsp;marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33230283","referenceCode":"EXN.2.SL.TZ0.8d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the probability that at least five of them will take more than 30 minutes to complete the jigsaw puzzle.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}